            "format": "basic_html",
            "processed": "<p>A generalist framework for multi-dimensional automatic spot detection and quantification.</p><p>SpotMAX is designed to accomplish two tasks:</p><ol><li>Detecting and quantifying globular-like structures (a.k.a. \"spots\")</li><li>Segmenting and quantifying fluorescently labelled structures</li></ol><p>It supports 2D, 3D, 4D, and 5D data, i.e., z-stacks, timelapse, and multiple fluorescence channels (and combinations thereof).</p>",
            "summary": "",
            "value": "<p>A generalist framework for multi-dimensional automatic spot detection and quantification.</p><p>SpotMAX is designed to accomplish two tasks:</p><ol><li>Detecting and quantifying globular-like structures (a.k.a. \"spots\")</li><li>Segmenting and quantifying fluorescently labelled structures</li></ol><p>It supports 2D, 3D, 4D, and 5D data, i.e., z-stacks, timelapse, and multiple fluorescence channels (and combinations thereof).</p>"
